main event: An unidentified object was observed and later identified as a balloon in Snow Hill, Maryland on October 20, 1965.
interesting points: The object was identified as a balloon launched by NASA from Wallops Island,The balloon was made of metallized mylar plastic and had a blimp-like shape,The object generated public interest after it landed approximately 25 miles inland from Wallops Island,The Air Force UFO Information Office classified the incident as marginal after investigation,The balloon was connected to experimental tests being conducted by the Langley Research Center.
witness description: Mrs. George Thonkpins, owner of the hatchery where the object was found.
